MBOMBELA – Numerous complaints were received from members of the public who were left waiting for hours at Nelspruit Police Station charge office.  A reliable source took this video of the empty rooms at the charge office.  Police spokesman Capt Dawie Pretorius denied the allegation that substandard  service was given at the station. ALSO READ : BREAKING NEWS: Police debunk hostage rumours as Makro workers resume strike     